Leaders of the 16 countries which have the British monarch as their head of state agree to change succession laws so that sons and daughters of the monarch have equal succession rights and can marry a Roman Catholic. (BBC) (The Telegraph)Prime Minister of the Netherlands Mark Rutte tenders his government's resignation to Queen Beatrix, paving the way for early elections. (BBC) (NOS)Police in Swaziland detain at least seven activists on their way to a pro-democracy church service in the city of Manzini. (IOL)